## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="bc4db-395">Die Platzhalterelement ist bis zum Ende der aktuellen Sequenz von Elementen hinzugefügt.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc4db-395">The wildcard element is added to the end of the current sequence of elements.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="bc4db-396">Die Platzhalterelement entspricht jedes gesprochenes Wort.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc4db-396">The wildcard element matches any spoken word.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="bc4db-397">Er entspricht nicht Hintergrundgeräuschen oder Pausen.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc4db-397">It does not match background noise or silence.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="bc4db-398">Das folgende Beispiel erstellt eine Grammatik, die Kennwort als Platzhalter akzeptiert.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc4db-398">The following example creates a grammar that accepts password input as a wildcard.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="bc4db-399">Im Beispiel fügt eine <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType> -Ereignishandler der Grammatik, die die Kennworteingabe überprüft.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc4db-399">The example attaches a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType> event handler to the grammar that validates the password input.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
private Grammar CreatePasswordGrammar()  
{  
  GrammarBuilder wildcardBuilder = new GrammarBuilder();  
  wildcardBuilder.AppendWildcard();  
  SemanticResultKey passwordKey =  
    new SemanticResultKey("Password", wildcardBuilder);  
  
  GrammarBuilder passwordBuilder =  
    new GrammarBuilder("My Password is");  
  passwordBuilder.Append(passwordKey);  
  
  Grammar passwordGrammar = new Grammar(passwordBuilder);  
  passwordGrammar.Name = "Password input";  
  
  passwordGrammar.SpeechRecognized +=  
    new EventHandler<SpeechRecognizedEventArgs>(  
      PasswordInputHandler);  
  
  return passwordGrammar;  
}  
  
// Handle the SpeechRecognized event for the password grammar.  
private void PasswordInputHandler(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
{  
  if (e.Result == null) return;  
  
  RecognitionResult result = e.Result;  
  SemanticValue semantics = e.Result.Semantics;  
  
  if (semantics.ContainsKey("Password"))  
  {  
    RecognizedAudio passwordAudio =  
      result.GetAudioForWordRange(  
        result.Words[3], result.Words[result.Words.Count - 1]);  
  
    if (IsValidPassword(passwordAudio))  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("Password accepted.");  
  
      // Add code to handle a valid password here.  
    }  
    else  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("Invalid password.");  
  
      // Add code to handle an invalid password here.  
    }  
  }  
}  
  
// Validate the password input.   
private bool IsValidPassword(RecognizedAudio passwordAudio)  
{  
  Console.WriteLine("Validating password.");  
  
  // Add password validation code here.  
  
  return false;  
}  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="bc4db-403">Die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.%23ctor%2A> Konstruktor erstellt ein <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> -Objekt, das von einer Spracherkennung der entsprechenden Kultur verwendet werden kann.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc4db-403">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.%23ctor%2A> constructor creates a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> object that can be used by a speech recognizer of the corresponding culture.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="bc4db-404">Nur die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder.Culture%2A> Eigenschaft von der <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> , die bereitgestellt wird, wie der Parameter an den Konstruktor Grammatik verwendet wird, die Kultur der resultierenden Speech Recognition Grammatik festlegen.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc4db-404">Only the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder.Culture%2A> property of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> that is provided as the parameter to the Grammar constructor is used to set the culture of the resulting speech recognition grammar.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="bc4db-405">Übernehmen alle gültigen Sprache / Land-Codes, Microsoft Windows und die System.Speech-API.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc4db-405">Microsoft Windows and the System.Speech API accept all valid language-country codes.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="bc4db-406">Mit der Sprache, die im angegebenen Spracherkennung Ausführen der `Culture` -Eigenschaft, ein Spracherkennungsmodul, die Sprache / Land-Code installiert werden muss unterstützt.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc4db-406">To perform speech recognition using the language specified in the `Culture` property, a speech recognition engine that supports that language-country code must be installed.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="bc4db-407">Die Spracherkennungsmoduls, die mit den im Lieferumfang von Microsoft Windows 7 arbeiten Sie mit der folgenden Sprache / Land-Codes.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc4db-407">The speech recognition engines that shipped with Microsoft Windows 7 work with the following language-country codes.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="bc4db-408">en-GB.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc4db-408">en-GB.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="bc4db-409">Englisch (Großbritannien)</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc4db-409">English (United Kingdom)</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="bc4db-410">En-US.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc4db-410">en-US.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="bc4db-411">Englisch (Vereinigte Staaten)</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc4db-411">English (United States)</span></span>  
  
